Disaster Recovery focuses on restoring services after major failures.

Important concepts:

* Recovery Time Objective (RTO)
* Recovery Point Objective (RPO)
* Backup strategies
* Failover planning

For example, a company replicates workloads to another region for recovery.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is protecting financial applications from regional outages.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is recovering business systems after cyber incidents.

Disaster Recovery ensures business continuity.
